There is a database named "userdb" owned by user.

I will connect to "userdb" and list tables:

Command: \c userdb; \dt; SELECT * FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema='public';

The "userdb" database contains three tables: customers, orders, products.

I will query the customers table for any sensitive data.

Command: SELECT * FROM customers LIMIT 10;

Customer data from the database retrieved including names and emails.

Next, I will query the orders and products tables to check for further useful data.

Commands:

SELECT * FROM orders LIMIT 5;

SELECT * FROM products LIMIT 5;
